gh how to achieve this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring JaCoCo and reflections**\\n\\nI’m considering how to make a reflection call to a holder class in the test package using `Class.forName` within a native image. Since the user-code-filter allows for that package, there could be metadata. However, at runtime, the class needs to be initialized. There’s a chance that `Class#getDeclaredFields` returns more than one field due to JaCoCo instrumentation, which could lead to test failures if it includes the `$jacocoData` synthetic field. I’ll need to check if all test classes get instrumented and consider using a holder that avoids this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing Struct and JaCoCo interactions**\\n\\nI’m looking at whether the Struct's holder has a direct default entry and if it’s potentially free of JaCoCo. When I check `getMapDefaultEntry` using `Struct.class` with \\\"fields,\\\" it returns the `Struct$FieldsDefaultEntryHolder`, which isn’t instrumented, and the fields length is 1. I realize I can use `Struct.class` with \\\"fields\\\" instead of my test class. However, the holder is a private class and inaccessible, so I might need to assert an instance of `MapEntryLite` and use Struct parsing instead.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rDSI9aj2AVY3Of0yFsfngeou|fc_04adbf90e6d093540169f2d331c7f0819d9fb166541e9e1a72", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-javalite/3.25.5/src/test/java/com_google_protobuf/protobuf_javalite/SchemaUtilTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertSame;\n\nimport com.google.protobuf.MapEntryLite;\nimport com.google.protobuf.SchemaUtilAccess;\nimport com.google.protobuf.WireFormat;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n", "newText": "import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertInstanceOf;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertNotNull;\n\nimport com.google.protobuf.MapEntryLite;\nimport com.google.protobuf.SchemaUtilAccess;\nimport com.google.protobuf.Struct;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n"}, {"oldText": "    public void mapDefaultEntryHolderIsResolvedFromMessageClassAndFieldName() {\n        Object defaultEntry = SchemaUtilAccess.mapDefaultEntry(MapDefaultEntryMessage.class, \"labels\");\n\n        assertSame(MapDefaultEntryMessage.LabelsDefaultEntryHolder.defaultEntry, defaultEntry);\n    }\n\n    private static final class MapDefaultEntryMessage {\n        private static final class LabelsDefaultEntryHolder {\n            static final MapEntryLite<String, Integer> defaultEntry =\n                    MapEntryLite.newDefaultInstance(\n                            WireFormat.FieldType.STRING, \"\", WireFormat.FieldType.INT32, 0);\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    public void mapDefaultEntryHolderIsResolvedFromMessageClassAndFieldName() {\n        Object defaultEntry = SchemaUtilAccess.mapDefaultEntry(Struct.class, \"fields\");\n\n        assertInstanceOf(MapEntryLite.class, defaultEntry);\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 552, "output": 1048, "cacheRead": 44032, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 45632, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777521443980, "responseId": "resp_04adbf90e6d093540169f2d324ae64819dbd216b8473390d57"}}
